  "name": "Envision Creation",
  "type": "feat",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<div><p><strong>Trigger</strong> You are about to Cast a Spell that takes 2 or 3 actions.</p><hr /></div><p>You can envision your next masterpiece in advance, and with your art of spell creation, picturing it is half the process of making it. When you cast your catalyzed spell, you contribute 1 action towards your spell with this action, and ready the spell to be cast at any point before the end of your next turn.</p><p>You must contribute the remaining actions to your spell to complete it by then, or else you will lose the spell. You resolve any reactions or interactions with the act of casting the spell when you use this action and when you complete your spell. You cannot modify the readied spell in any way during this time, such as with other catalysts or spellshapes, and you cannot cast any other spells until you complete the spell or forgo it.</p><p><strong>Visionary Catalyst</strong> You only incur reactions when you begin casting the spell, not when you complete the spell.</p>"
